Job Description:
Since its inception in 2013, the CRE Debt Team has successfully invested over $6 billion across four investment vehicles and various separate accounts. To date, the majority of capital deployed has been in floating rate transitional first mortgage loans secured by major property types in key markets throughout the United States. Through strategic growth, with offices on both the East and West Coasts, the team is well positioned to capitalize on opportunities to invest in markets across the U.S.  We are in the process of launching new investment vehicles with the intention to expand the investment profile to include mezzanine loans, distressed debt, fixed rate loans, construction loans and net lease investments. Established processes and systems are in place to reinforce the discipline required to excel across all facets of the broadened investment mandate, including experienced deal sourcing, meticulous underwriting, comprehensive investor reporting and proven asset management.  The candidate will have an outstanding opportunity to develop a broad range of financial, analytical, marketing, and presentation skills.
We are seeking an Analyst/Associate based in New York to join our Real Estate Debt group in a portfolio management function. The candidate will be supporting the portfolio management team in internal loan summary reporting and external portfolio level reporting, reconciling servicing reports to internal fund ledgers, and maintaining the fund portfolio models.
Specific responsibilities of this role may include but not be limited to:
Completion of daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly and annual tasks related to portfolio management and investor reporting;
Reconciliation of cash transactions within the portfolio model;
Assist with the preparation of other recurring summaries, such as fund reporting, capital activity projections, loan allocations, ratings, fund forecasts, and scenario analysis;
Compile portfolio level financial roll-ups and performance measurements for internal and external reporting;
Assist with the development and buildout of functionality for a cloud-based database to replace the current Excel based portfolio model;
Maintain a cash management model, tracking used and unused capacities, costs, and covenant compliance for financing facilities;
Review and allocate fund expenses;
Monitor and execute the FX hedging program;
Develop strong relationships and effective lines of communication with internal departments/personnel and externally with investors and service providers, such as diligent management and coordination of tasks with loan servicers;
Assist with originations, investor relations, and other departments with ad-hoc special projects and assignments
Job Qualifications: 
Bachelor’s Degree with 3-5 years of experience in real estate and/or financial services operational experience
Excellent computer skills including Microsoft Office (Excel, PowerPoint)
Ability to manage multiple projects concurrently
Strong attention to detail
Experience with Database tools  
AllianceBernstein (AB) is a global investment-management firm providing industry-leading research and investment solutions through a combination of innovation, intellectual curiosity and relentless ingenuity. We offer high-quality research and diversified investment services to institutional and individual investors worldwide. Our clients include some of the world's top institutions as well as private-wealth clients and retail investors. Through close partnerships with our clients, we collaborate on investment strategies across regions and sectors to inspire innovative thinking and deliver superior outcomes. 
We invest in our people and in the communities in which we operate, and we celebrate our diversity to showcase what makes us unique. We offer our talent the opportunity to grow professionally while working on cutting-edge ideas and outcomes in a global culture that operates as a tight-knit community. 
If you're ready to innovate and grow your career, join us. 
People of color, women, and those who identify as LGBTQ people are encouraged to apply. AB does not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment on the basis of race, color, religion, creed,  ancestry, national origin, sex, age, disability, marital status, citizenship status, sexual orientation, gender identity, military or veteran status or any other basis that is prohibited by applicable law.  AB’s policies, as well as practices, seek to ensure that employment opportunities are available to all employees and applicants, based solely on job-related criteria.
